# Browser Automation Rules

## Stagehand (AI-native Playwright by Browserbase)
Stagehand wraps Playwright with AI understanding of page structure.
Use it for all form-filling — it handles dynamic/complex application forms
that traditional selectors would break on.

Import: import { Stagehand } from '@browserbasehq/stagehand'

## Cloud Browser (Browserbase)
Always run in Browserbase cloud — never local Playwright in production.
Local Playwright only in development/testing.

```typescript
const stagehand = new Stagehand({
  env: 'BROWSERBASE',
  apiKey: process.env.BROWSERBASE_API_KEY,
  projectId: process.env.BROWSERBASE_PROJECT_ID,
  verbose: 1
})
```

## Application Extraction (src/lib/browser/extract.ts)
When given a job URL:
1. Open in Stagehand
2. Extract: { title, company, description, applicationUrl, requiredFields }
3. Close browser
4. Return structured JobPosting object

## Application Submission (src/lib/browser/apply.ts)
Flow:
1. Open application URL in Stagehand
2. Identify all form fields (Stagehand's `page.observe()`)
3. Classify each field (name, email, CV upload, cover letter, open-ended Q)
4. Fill using Stagehand's `page.act()` for each field
5. Pause before final submit — take screenshot, return for user confirmation
6. After user confirms: complete submission
7. Return: { success, confirmationText, screenshotUrl }

## Field Classification
| Field Type | How to Fill |
|---|---|
| name / email / phone / location | Pull from userPreferences directly |
| CV upload | Upload tailored CV as PDF (generate from JSON) |
| cover letter textarea | Inject generated cover letter text |
| "Why do you want to work here?" | Generate fresh short-form answer via Claude |
| Salary | Use userPreferences.salaryExpectation |
| Work authorization yes/no | userPreferences.workAuthorization |
| Open-ended (anything else) | Generate via Claude with job context |

## Open-Ended Question Handling
For any field not in the list above:
  const answer = await generateFieldAnswer({
    question: fieldLabel,
    jobAnalysis,
    userProfile,
    maxWords: 150
  })
Use a dedicated mini-prompt for this — not the full CV pipeline.

## Rules
- Never submit without taking a final screenshot for user review
- Log every field filled: { fieldLabel, valueSummary, timestamp }
- Timeout: 90 seconds per application — if exceeded, fail gracefully with screenshot
- On error: save session screenshot, throw structured error with field that failed